
/** Author: Monica DRAGAN, for GSoc 2013 **/

The program builds a id3 tree for discrete input values.

The datastructures used to store the dataset are:
CMulticlassLabels - for iterating through samples and for the classes
CDenseFeatures - a matrix for all the samples


The lables of sample data are codified in positive integers.
For a human readable display of the ID3 tree, the name of the lables are give by hand by the user (for the moment). 

The Data in classifier_id3_meteo.dat file represents a codification of the followinf dataset:

OVERCAST	TEMPERATURE	HUMIDITY	WIND	CLASS
sunny		worm       	high       false      N
sunny      	worm       	high       true       N
cloudy     	worm      	high       false      P
rain    	fine     	high       false      P
rain   	 	cold     	normal     false      P
rain    	cold     	normal     true       N
cloudy      cold     	normal     true       P
sunny     	fine     	high       false      N
sunny    	cold     	normal     false      P
rain    	fine      	normal     false      P
sunny     	fine      	normal     true       P
cloudy      fine     	high       true       P
cloudy      worm        normal     false      P
rain    	fine     	high       true       N

** Compile & Run **
$ g++ -O0 -g -I/usr/include -I/usr/include/atlas -I/usr/include/eigen3 -lshogun -L/usr/local/lib  classifier_multiclass_id3.cpp  -o classifier
$ ./classifier

